President Obama expresses his satisfaction with the Senate confirming Penny Pritzker as the Secretary of Commerce. He highlights her leadership qualities, success as an entrepreneur, and her esteemed reputation in the business world. The President believes that Pritzker's experience in building companies from scratch aligns with his vision of supporting businesses and workers to create more job opportunities in America. He also emphasizes Pritzker's role as a crucial member of his economic team, focused on growing the economy and empowering the middle class.